README:
This BIDS data set contains the images described in this preprint: https://doi.org/10.1101/2022.11.04.515162 

The associated behavioural and eye-tracking data are available at https://github.com/carolfs/fmri_magic_carpet

trial_type.Description: Stage of each trial in the the two-stage task

Levels.first_stage: Choice between two carpets (story condition) or boxes (abstract condition)

slow.Description: If the participant missed the time limit for making a choice

Levels.0: The participant responded within the limit
Levels.n/a: When there was no choice to be made (feedback events)
